INSERT INTO Sessions (session_num, title, chapters, level_start, level_end, summary, key_encounters, key_npcs, dm_notes) VALUES
(1, 'Escape from Velkynvelve', 'Ch 1', 1, 2,
 'Players wake as prisoners in the drow outpost Velkynvelve. Meet fellow captives, assess the situation, and engineer an escape — whether through Jorlan''s betrayal, brute force, or cunning. The drow begin pursuit the moment the party is gone.',
 'Escape from Velkynvelve (hard). Equipment room heist. Webbed shaft / waterfall pool exit. Avoid waking Ilvara until the last moment.',
 'Ilvara Mizzrym (antagonist, awakened), Jorlan Duskryn (potential ally — give the master key if cultivated), Shoor Vandree (obstacle). Introduce all prisoner NPCs: Buppido, Prince Derendil, Eldeth, Jimjar, Ront, Sarith, Shuushar, Stool, Topsy & Turvy.',
 'Let Stool establish rapport spores early — it solves language barriers and creates instant NPC attachment. Eldeth''s bond (recover her gear) pays off in Part 2. Don''t let Buppido''s murderous secret show yet. Party has NO gear; reward creativity.'),
(2, 'Into Darkness: The Silken Paths', 'Ch 2', 2, 2,
 'The party flees through the Underdark with their ragtag group of former prisoners. Navigate the Silken Paths — a vast cavern strung with enormous spider webs — and begin the long trek toward a safe settlement. Ilvara''s pursuit begins in earnest.',
 'Silken Paths traversal (web collapses, giant spiders, optional mimic or spectator). 1-2 random Underdark encounters (use Ch2 creature/terrain tables). Drow Pursuit Escalation: first roll (15+ on d20 = caught).',
 'Shuushar: push him as Darklake guide. Sarith: begins having quiet, troubled moments (infection subplot). Topsy & Turvy: start showing stress — whisper more. Jimjar: bet on everything, use him for comic relief.',
 'This session is about atmosphere and NPC dynamics more than combat. Lean into Underdark weirdness: bioluminescence, strange fungi, alien scale. The Drow pursuit rolls create mounting tension. Buppido may ''misplace'' a companion''s pack — first seeds of his secret.'),
(3, 'Sloobludop & the Prince of Demons', 'Ch 3', 2, 3,
 'The party arrives at Sloobludop, the kuo-toa settlement on the Darklake shore. Caught between two fanatical cults — Ploopploopeen''s Sea Mother faction and Bloppblippodd''s Deep Father cult — the party is meant as sacrifices. The ritual is interrupted when the Deep Father answers: Demogorgon rises from the Darklake and destroys everything. RUN.',
 'Arrival at Sloobludop (cult confrontation, hard). Demogorgon Rises (survival set piece — unkillable, focus on escape to boats). Every round: Gaze attack DC 23, buildings collapsing, kuo-toa being slaughtered.',
 'Shuushar: shattered by what his home has become — play this for emotional weight. Ploopploopeen: plans to sacrifice party but is outmaneuvered. Bloppblippodd: her prayers literally called this.',
 'Demogorgon is NOT a fight. He is a force of nature. Give each PC a personal escape moment. Let the horror land — this is the first time players understand the true scale of what''s loose in the Underdark. Level up after escaping on the boats.'),
(4, 'The Darklake & Arrival at Gracklstugh', 'Ch 2–4', 3, 3,
 'The party crosses the Darklake by boat, navigating its alien waterways toward the City of Blades. Use 2-3 Darklake encounter rolls to fill travel. On arrival at Gracklstugh, the duergar are suspicious and the city is already showing signs of demonic madness — civilians fighting in the streets, stone giants rampaging.',
 '2-3 Darklake creature/terrain encounters (aquatic troll, ixitxachitl, rough current, etc.). Gracklstugh gate: duergar guards demand toll and papers. City encounter: derro rioters or mad duergar in Blade Bazaar.',
 'Errde Blackskull: hires party to investigate the madness. Ylsa Henstak: merchant contact, market access. Buppido: arriving home — his demeanor shifts, becomes more purposeful (suspicious).',
 'Gracklstugh is a slow-burn paranoia city. Duergar are universally hostile to outsiders. Establish that something is deeply wrong: the city''s rigid order is cracking. Themberchaud''s silhouette visible above the city — tease him before the reveal.'),
(5, 'Gracklstugh: City of Madness', 'Ch 4', 3, 4,
 'Investigate the demonic madness consuming Gracklstugh. Delve into the Whorlstone Tunnels beneath the city to find derro Demogorgon cultists. Navigate the politics of the Keepers of the Flame and the Gray Ghosts. Culminates in an audience with Themberchaud, who wants information — and is dangerously close to snapping.',
 'Whorlstone Tunnels (multiple encounters: carrion crawlers, demons, two-headed grimlocks). Themberchaud — Dragon Audience (deadly, but MUST NOT become combat). Use his paranoia as a lever for a distraction or a favor.',
 'Themberchaud (CR17 — paranoid, wants truth). Errde Blackskull: debrief and reward. Buppido REVEAL: if party notices missing supplies or a dead NPC, Buppido is the killer — confront him here or in the tunnels. He fights to the death believing he is divine.',
 'Buppido''s reveal is the big emotional beat of this session. Time it for maximum drama — find a body, then confront him. Themberchaud audience is a masterclass in tension: he COULD kill everyone, but he just wants the truth. Reward info generously from him. Level up after resolving the dragon.'),
(6, 'Neverlight Grove: The Fetid Wedding', 'Ch 5', 4, 5,
 'Stool leads the party to Neverlight Grove to return home — but the grove has been transformed. Bioluminescent beauty hides creeping horror: Zuggtmoy is conducting her wedding ritual, and the myconids are almost entirely subverted. Sovereign Basidia is the only hope. The party must uncover the truth and escape before being invited to the wedding themselves.',
 'Neverlight encounters (chasme, nothics near corrupted circles). Zuggtmoy''s Wedding scene: DC 15 Con save vs. spore infection if they enter the rotunda. Escape while Basidia seals the tunnels.',
 'Stool: homecoming horror. Sovereign Phylo (hostile/corrupted): honeyed invitations, weeping spores. Sovereign Basidia (ally): the key to escaping and to understanding Zuggtmoy. Sarith: his infection peaks here — he either fully turns or dies trying to protect the party.',
 'Sarith''s arc ends here. Make it tragic. The grove should feel like a fairy tale gone wrong — beautiful, wrong, suffocating. Don''t let players fight Zuggtmoy. The goal is escape with Basidia''s help. Level up after warning Basidia and escaping.'),
(7, 'Blingdenstone: The Pudding King''s Court', 'Ch 6', 5, 6,
 'The deep gnome city of Blingdenstone is under siege from within: ooze colonies and the mad spirit of the Pudding King (a gnome consumed by Juiblex) have claimed the Goldwhisker Quarter and the old residential warrens. The gnomes desperately need help. Topsy and Turvy''s wererat kin live here — their secret may finally surface.',
 'Roaming ooze encounters in haunted districts. Pudding King''s Domain (black puddings + gray oozes). The Pudding King''s Court (hard): The Pudding King + 2 black puddings + Elder Ooze — boss fight.',
 'Topsy & Turvy REVEAL: their wererat kin are in Goldwhisker Quarter. The twins'' lycanthropy transformation is forced here. Give players a choice: help them control it, or let them go to their kin. The gnomes: grateful, reward with gems, surface route, and safe passage.',
 'Topsy and Turvy''s arc resolves here — sympathetically if handled well. The Pudding King speaks in rhyming couplets; lean into the absurd horror. Defeating him ends the ooze infestation and earns the party full gnome support. Level up here — milestone before the surface.'),
(8, 'Escape to the Surface & the Council of Waterdeep', 'Ch 7–10', 6, 8,
 'COMPRESSED. The party finally escapes the Underdark. Run the surface arrival as a brief emotional beat — sunlight, fresh air, the weight of what they survived. Ilvara makes one last pursuit attempt (final Part 1 confrontation). Then, fast-forward: the party delivers their report. The Council of Waterdeep convenes. Surface factions debrief the party and send them back — with resources, allies, and a mission.',
 'Ilvara''s Final Pursuit (hard): Ilvara wounded + Jorlan (possible ally switch) + 4 drow. Council of Waterdeep: roleplaying/social encounter. Grant 2 levels (6→8) to reflect the narrative skip.',
 'Ilvara: furious, reckless, uses Suggestion. Jorlan: switches sides if cultivated — cathartic payoff. Eldeth: if alive, reunites her shield with Bruenor''s kin. Bruenor Battlehammer: brief appearance, sets up Part 2. Surface faction representatives at Council.',
 'This session is the hinge of the campaign. Part 1 ends with Ilvara''s defeat — make it feel earned. The Council scene should be fast (30 min max): here is the threat, here are your resources, go. The double level-up (6→8) represents the mission briefing and travel prep montage. Part 2 begins.'),
(9, 'Return to the Underdark: Mantol-Derith', 'Ch 11', 8, 9,
 'The party descends again — this time with a dwarven escort and resources. Their first destination: Mantol-Derith, the neutral trading post, which is the gateway to Vizeran''s tower. They find it in chaos. Demogorgon''s madness has broken the four-faction truce and the settlement is a warzone. The party must navigate without drawing fire from any side.',
 'Mantol-Derith Faction War (hard): four factions — drow, duergar, svirfneblin, mind flayer — all hostile to each other. Find Harper agent Khalessa Draga (poisoned, needs rescue). First PC to draw a weapon triggers everyone. Each faction has one piece of the truth.',
 'Grazilaxx the mind flayer: information broker, can be traded with carefully. Khalessa Draga: Harper agent, desperate for rescue, knows the route to Vizeran. The four faction leaders: each paranoid, each partly right.',
 'The challenge is that ALL sides are hostile and the party must thread the needle. Reward clever neutrality — give intelligence bonuses for extracting info from multiple factions without combat. Khalessa is the objective. Level up after reaching safety and securing her intel.'),
(10, 'Vizeran''s Tower: The Dark Heart Bargain', 'Ch 12', 9, 10,
 'The party reaches Araj, Vizeran DeVir''s hidden tower. The ancient exile archmage has a plan to banish all demon lords at once — his Dark Heart ritual. He needs components the party must gather: the eye of a demon lord, Demogorgon''s brain, Yeenoghu''s heart, Zuggtmoy''s spores, Juiblex''s slime, and the Maze Engine. He provides maps, magic, and his tower as a base. Plant seeds of his true agenda.',
 'Trap navigation in the tower approach (Vizeran''s wards). The meeting itself is a high-stakes social encounter — Vizeran is brilliant, arrogant, and hiding something.',
 'Vizeran DeVir: give him the full treatment — ancient, contemptuous, utterly certain of his superiority. He will not suffer fools. Plant one clear tell of his true goal (offhand comment about Menzoberranzan deserving what''s coming). Let sharp players catch it.',
 'The component list is the Part 2 quest structure. Lay it all out clearly so players can plan. The tower is now their base. Vizeran''s true plan (using the ritual to destroy Menzoberranzan) is the campaign''s central moral question — introduce the doubt HERE so it has time to build. Level up after the bargain is struck.'),
(11, 'The Wormwrithings: Yeenoghu''s Hunt', 'Ch 13', 10, 11,
 'The party enters the Wormwrithings — vast tunnels bored by purple worms — to gather Yeenoghu''s heart (kill or steal from the demon lord of gnolls). Yeenoghu has established a hunting ground here, driving gnoll warbands through the region. The party must navigate purple worm tunnel collapses, gnoll ambushes, and eventually face or outmaneuver Yeenoghu himself.',
 'Wormwrithings encounters (purple worms, gnoll packs, ettins). Yeenoghu confrontation: he is CR 24 — direct combat is possible at level 10-11 if the party is clever and uses the terrain. Extracting his heart requires a killing blow or a desperate ritual.',
 'No key named NPCs — Yeenoghu is a force. Play him as savage and joyful in the hunt. If gnolls are encountered, one pack may be desperate and negotiable (they fear Yeenoghu too).',
 'This is a more pure action session. Wormwrithings is all about the physical horror of the terrain — tunnels that shift, purple worms that could appear anywhere. Yeenoghu is genuinely killable at this level if the party is coordinated. Reward creative use of the environment. Level up after securing his heart.'),
(12, 'The Labyrinth: The Maze Engine', 'Ch 14', 11, 12,
 'Deep in Baphomet''s shifting maze, the party must locate and activate the Maze Engine — an ancient modron artifact that can alter reality. Baphomet hunts them personally. The engine activation triggers wild magic effects and, if used correctly, can be configured as a component in Vizeran''s ritual to force-banish demon lords.',
 'Labyrinth encounters (minotaurs, gnolls, hezrous, behir). Maze Engine Activation (deadly): Baphomet + 4 minotaurs guarding the antechamber. Activate the engine while Baphomet closes in — d10 wild magic table fires.',
 'Baphomet: CR 23, hunts by sound and smell. He is patient and intelligent despite his bestial form. The maze shifts around him. A lone monodrone wandering the labyrinth can provide a cryptic clue about the engine.',
 'Escape is a completely valid strategy — the engine just needs to be activated, not the party victorious in combat. Baphomet''s bellowing should get louder each hour (sound-based countdown). The wild magic table effects are fun chaos — lean into the modron weirdness. Level up after escaping with the engine data.'),
(13, 'Gathering the Remaining Components', 'Ch 12–16', 12, 13,
 'MONTAGE SESSION. The party collects the final ritual components: Juiblex''s slime (from the Endless Nadir), Zuggtmoy''s spores (a mission back near Araumycos), and a drow exile-heart from Vizeran himself. As components come together, investigation reveals the full truth of Vizeran''s plan — the ritual will destroy Menzoberranzan.',
 'Juiblex encounter (Ch 12-area): survival-focused, Juiblex is CR 23 — extract a slime sample and flee. Zuggtmoy spore extraction near Araumycos (Araumycos travel encounters). The True Plan Reveal: arcana check DC 20 on the ritual documents, or a direct confrontation with Vizeran.',
 'Vizeran: the confrontation about his true plan. He does not apologize — Menzoberranzan is a blight that caused all of this. He is not wrong, but he is monstrous. The party must decide: use his ritual as-is, modify it (DC 20 Arcana), or find another way.',
 'This is the campaign''s moral climax. There is no clean answer. Menzoberranzan is full of civilians. It also spawned Gromph''s ritual. Vizeran is both villain and necessary. Give the party real time to debate. The arcana modification is hard (DC 20) but possible — reward preparation and roleplaying. Level up when all components are secured.'),
(14, 'Menzoberranzan: Infiltration', 'Ch 15', 13, 14,
 'The party must enter the City of Spiders to position the Dark Heart ritual components at the city''s center — Narbondellyn. This requires infiltrating the most heavily guarded drow city in the Underdark, navigating district patrols, potentially meeting Matron Mother Triel Baenre, and confronting Gromph Baenre — the man responsible for everything.',
 'Menzoberranzan entry patrols (drow patrols escalating). District navigation (Blade Bazaar, Narbondellyn, noble tier). Gromph confrontation: revelation scene, not combat — he caused all of this and will not apologize. Optional: Triel negotiation.',
 'Gromph Baenre: the revelation. He is guilty, denies it, and is furious at being cornered. Triel Baenre: cold negotiation — she wants the demons gone and will not admit weakness. Bregan D''aerthe mercenaries: potential neutral ground.',
 'The Gromph scene is the campaign''s explanation moment — give it weight. Don''t rush it. The city should feel enormous and overwhelming — everywhere the party looks, drow are going about their lives unaware of what''s about to happen. This makes the moral choice about Vizeran''s plan hit harder. Level up after positioning the components.'),
(15, 'Araumycos: The World Fungus', 'Ch 16', 14, 14,
 'Final component delivery and ritual preparation. The party travels through Araumycos — the continent-spanning fungal organism that Zuggtmoy is trying to possess. This is a surreal, dreamlike session. If Zuggtmoy has had time, the merger is close and the region is actively hostile. This is also the last chance to finalize modifications to the ritual before the finale.',
 'Araumycos travel encounters (demon sortie waves, myconid parades, oozes, two-headed trolls). Zuggtmoy presence: the fungal matter reacts to the party. The closer they are to her merger point, the more dangerous it becomes.',
 'Basidia (if alive) can appear here via rapport spores with Stool — a last message of hope or warning. The fungal colony itself has a dim, alien sentience that the party may sense.',
 'Lean into the alien beauty and wrongness of Araumycos. This is the last session before the finale — use it to let players reflect on what they''ve survived and make final preparations. Let them ask questions, set up tactics, and say what their characters are thinking. The calm before the storm.'),
(16, 'The Dark Heart Ritual: End of the Incursion', 'Ch 17', 14, 15,
 'Vizeran completes the Dark Heart ritual at Menzoberranzan''s heart. All demon lords are drawn to one place — and the party must hold the ritual site for 10 rounds while hell breaks loose. Waves of demons attack. The lords themselves arrive. On round 10, the ritual fires and every demon lord is banished back to the Abyss. The outcome (does Menzoberranzan survive?) depends on what the party chose.',
 'Demon Sortie Waves (rounds 1-9, one wave per 2 rounds): barlguras, chasmes, hezrous, vrocks. Battle Chaos Events (d6 each round: explosions, debris). Final Round: all demon lords manifest — Demogorgon, Juiblex, Zuggtmoy, Baphomet, Yeenoghu. Ritual fires. Describe each banishment individually.',
 'Vizeran: casting for 10 rounds, cannot be interrupted without ending the ritual. He is both the hero and the villain of this moment. Surviving NPCs who traveled with the party should be present — give them a moment in the finale.',
 'Describe each demon lord''s banishment in a unique way — Demogorgon''s twin heads screaming as they''re pulled apart by the vortex, Zuggtmoy''s spores being burned away, Baphomet''s roar fading into silence. If the party modified the ritual: Menzoberranzan survives. If not: describe the city''s fate honestly and let it land. End with the Underdark beginning to quiet. The incursion is over.')
